{
  "_comment": "Curated catalog of models providers can serve via /v1/chat/completions, refreshed July 2026 and tag-verified against the live Ollama registry (registry.ollama.ai) so every entry is actually pullable. Each entry carries approx on-disk size (Q4-class `sizeGb`), a conservative minimum accelerator-memory floor (`minRamGb` \u2014 the memory the weights + context must fit in: Apple Silicon = unified memory; NVIDIA = VRAM; CPU = capped system RAM. The dispatcher gates fit on the node's reported `acceleratorMemGb`/`accel`, falling back to legacy `ram`), a `type` (text|code|vision), and `tags` capability badges (reasoning, tools, agentic, code, general, fast, vision, grounding, moe, rag). Served at /models/catalog; the installer, `koretex models`, `koretex autoserve`, and the pre-install `koretex-preview` script filter by the machine's actual accelerator RAM + free disk (fit = minRamGb<=accel AND sizeGb+10<=freeDisk) and show the badges. `primary` marks the model the network most wants. pointsWeight and price are derived server-side from the tag (modelWeight parses the param count; pricing.rate falls back for unpriced tags) \u2014 new tags are safe to add. The ceiling is high-end CONSUMER Apple Silicon: most entries target 8-256GB Macs/GPUs, and a few frontier MoE (Qwen3-Coder 480B, DeepSeek V3.1 671B) carry 320-512GB floors so they only surface on a maxed M3 Ultra Mac Studio \u2014 nothing needs datacenter GPUs. VISION (VLM) models serve over the SAME /v1/chat/completions path (image in, text out) and are allowed, but kept out of the tok/s hardware metric (image prefill distorts throughput). Embedding/image-gen models need other endpoints and stay excluded (filtered server-side). A `tag` is normally an Ollama-library name (`qwen3:8b`); it can also be a HuggingFace GGUF via Ollama passthrough (`hf.co/<org>/<repo>:<QUANT>`). Ollama serves/bills the LOWERCASED id (pricing + points are case-insensitive). Grow this list with what customers actually demand.",
